Change the grade checks to an if / else if / else chain, for example:

if (grade >= 90) {
    System.out.println("A");
} else if (grade >= 80) {
    System.out.println("B");
} else if (grade >= 70) {
    System.out.println("C");
} else if (grade >= 60) {
    System.out.println("D");
} else {
    System.out.println("F");
}

This way, only the first true condition runs, and exactly one letter grade is printed.

